  context={"endpoint"}
>
  
</MethodEndpoint>



Gets a link containing the transactional account details associated with an addressing key.

### Requests limitation
Key consultation is subject to the rate-limiting policy for requests.
Throttling works based on headers sent in the request. Request headers are required
for all types of keys.

The `PI-PayerId` parameter is the end-user identifier and is used to enforce payment policies.
limitation with user scope. It must be filled in with the CPF or CNPJ (only digits), depending on
of the type of entity holding the paying account.

### Statistics
Through the optional `IncludeStatistics` parameter, it is possible to indicate whether the anti-fraud counter information
should or should not be included in the response.

### Retry recomendations
This endpoint implements retry flow on a specific HTTP Status and ErrorCode.**

> In case of HTTP Status 503 and ErrorCode PBE7026, it is highly recommended to perform retries until receiving a HTTP Status 200.

            1)](https://s3.sa-east-1.amazonaws.com/dev.developer-portal-landing-page/images/dict-get-key-retry-flowchart.jpg)
